{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.68",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 68,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 68 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:1",
      "text": "Let God arise, let his enemies be scattered; let those who hate him flee before him!",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:2",
      "text": "As smoke is driven away, so drive them away; as wax melts before fire, let the wicked perish before God!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:3",
      "text": "But let the righteous be joyful; let them exult before God; let them be jubilant with joy!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:4",
      "text": "Sing to God, sing praises to his name; lift up a song to him who rides upon the clouds; his name is the Lord, exult before him!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:5",
      "text": "Father of the fatherless and protector of widows is God in his holy habitation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:6",
      "text": "God gives the desolate a home to dwell in; he leads out the prisoners to prosperity; but the rebellious dwell in a parched land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:7",
      "text": "O God, when thou didst go forth before thy people, when thou didst march through the wilderness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:8",
      "text": "the earth quaked, the heavens poured down rain, at the presence of God; yon Sinai quaked at the presence of God, the God of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:9",
      "text": "Rain in abundance, O God, thou didst shed abroad; thou didst restore thy heritage as it languished;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:10",
      "text": "thy flock found a dwelling in it; in thy goodness, O God, thou didst provide for the needy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:11",
      "text": "The Lord gives the command; great is the host of those who bore the tidings:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:12",
      "text": "“The kings of the armies, they flee, they flee!” The women at home divide the spoil,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:13",
      "text": "though they stay among the sheepfolds— the wings of a dove covered with silver, its pinions with green gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:14",
      "text": "When the Almighty scattered kings there, snow fell on Zalmon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:15",
      "text": "O mighty mountain, mountain of Bashan; O many-peaked mountain, mountain of Bashan!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:16",
      "text": "Why look you with envy, O many-peaked mountain, at the mount which God desired for his abode, yea, where the Lord will dwell for ever?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:17",
      "text": "With mighty chariotry, twice ten thousand, thousands upon thousands, the Lord came from Sinai into the holy place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:18",
      "text": "Thou didst ascend the high mount, leading captives in thy train, and receiving gifts among men, even among the rebellious, that the Lord God may dwell there.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:19",
      "text": "Blessed be the Lord, who daily bears us up; God is our salvation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:20",
      "text": "Our God is a God of salvation; and to God, the Lord, belongs escape from death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:21",
      "text": "But God will shatter the heads of his enemies, the hairy crown of him who walks in his guilty ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:22",
      "text": "The Lord said, “I will bring them back from Bashan, I will bring them back from the depths of the sea,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:23",
      "text": "that you may bathe your feet in blood, that the tongues of your dogs may have their portion from the foe.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:24",
      "text": "Thy solemn processions are seen, O God, the processions of my God, my King, into the sanctuary—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:25",
      "text": "the singers in front, the minstrels last, between them maidens playing timbrels:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:26",
      "text": "“Bless God in the great congregation, the Lord, O you who are of Israel's fountain!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:27",
      "text": "There is Benjamin, the least of them, in the lead, the princes of Judah in their throng, the princes of Zebulun, the princes of Naphtali.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:28",
      "text": "Summon thy might, O God; show thy strength, O God, thou who hast wrought for us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:29",
      "text": "Because of thy temple at Jerusalem kings bear gifts to thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:30",
      "text": "Rebuke the beasts that dwell among the reeds, the herd of bulls with the calves of the peoples. Trample under foot those who lust after tribute; scatter the peoples who delight in war.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:31",
      "text": "Let bronze be brought from Egypt; let Ethiopia hasten to stretch out her hands to God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:32",
      "text": "Sing to God, O kingdoms of the earth; sing praises to the Lord,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:33",
      "text": "to him who rides in the heavens, the ancient heavens; lo, he sends forth his voice, his mighty voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:34",
      "text": "Ascribe power to God, whose majesty is over Israel, and his power is in the skies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.68.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 68,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 68:35",
      "text": "Terrible is God in his sanctuary, the God of Israel, he gives power and strength to his people. Blessed be God!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
